Launch Vm with image of openvpn from aws marketplace
connect the vm and get the admin and client url
connect with the url - user name and password is given in the connected vm .
connect the client url and download the client vpn software and connect the vpn. 
After successfully connected the vm . you can connect the private vm of the same network with out using public ip . 
the condition is simple all the vm should be in same vpc network to access them with private ip . 

chmod -R 400 Virginia-office.pem
ssh -i "virginia-office.pem" ec2-user@server-ip

allow the port number tcp/943 in private-server ec2 instance security group to ssh the vm
security group 
tcp/943

